.TH "omap3xxx_cm_wait_module_ready" 9 "omap3xxx_cm_wait_module_ready" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
omap3xxx_cm_wait_module_ready \- wait for a module to leave idle or standby
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" omap3xxx_cm_wait_module_ready
.BI "(u8 part "  ","
.BI "s16 prcm_mod "  ","
.BI "u16 idlest_id "  ","
.BI "u8 idlest_shift "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "part" 12
PRCM partition, ignored for OMAP3
.IP "prcm_mod" 12
PRCM module offset
.IP "idlest_id" 12
CM_IDLESTx register ID (i.e., x = 1, 2, 3)
.IP "idlest_shift" 12
shift of the bit in the CM_IDLEST* register to check
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Wait for the PRCM to indicate that the module identified by
(\fIprcm_mod\fP, \fIidlest_id\fP, \fIidlest_shift\fP) is clocked.  Return 0 upon
success or -EBUSY if the module doesn't enable in time.
